page.title: 10Fallow Deer
page.content: Combe Sydenham lies within the {Exmoor National Park. }This Park has as its symbol a Stag's head. In many areas of West Somerset it is possible to see the{Wild Red Deer}in its natural setting. At Combe Sydenham it is also possible to see the smaller and darker {Fallow Deer. }This is very much a parkland animal and here is contained within the original wrought iron fence. In the hot weather it is a fine sight to watch the deer resting under the large beech trees. It will be noticed that these Bucks have palmated antlers. The Does produce there young fawns in either May or June.
